          "storyText": "We’re two second-year CS students, and over the last 4 months we built a ML framework in Rust+CUDA with a TypeScript API on top (and a WebGPU fallback) Our goal is to fully understand the ML stack end-to-end. To force ourselves to use it for something real, we also trained a 12M-parameter transformer with it. We wrote custom CUDA kernels for operations such as flash attention, AdamW, layer norm, and GELU. We also added a WebGPU path so it can still run on machines without NVIDIA GPUs, though tha",
